baseline_groups.claim_summary: Duopoly entry in US cellular markets increases the number of foggy (dominated) tariff plans offered by wireline carriers.
baseline_groups.notes: Two-way FE (market + time), controls AP_PEAK + AP_OFFP, clustered at market level. Coef=0.314, p=0.125. The spec did/fe/twoway is an exact duplicate. Several control-addition specs produce identical estimates because added variables are collinear with market FE.

global_notes: 56 total specs. Baseline result is not statistically significant (p=0.125). Significance is highly sensitive to FE structure and clustering. Multiple specs are exact duplicates of baseline due to collinearity with market FE. Dynamic effects use different treatment variables (event-time indicators). Two alternative outcomes (log_PLANS_i, log_EFFPLi) measure different quantities than foggy plans.
